Simple test of the generic mux component (18 type-converting mux_generic instances).

Driven via the filestream cmod (was the WS streamer+sampler).  filestream advances
one input line per thread cycle, the deterministic pacing the live WS feed could not
reproduce.  All 18 mux outputs and the mux-gen.16 debounce match the classic golden
for every real-input row.

The `expected` was regenerated from the deterministic filestream output: the classic
golden's 5 trailing held-last rows carried a streamer-FIFO-overflow artifact (the
depth-100 FIFO held only 99 entries, so the 100th preloaded input line — the one
where sel flips to 1 — was dropped and the 99th was held instead).  filestream loads
all 100 input lines, so it correctly holds the 100th; the regenerated expected
reflects that (the 100 real-input rows were already byte-identical to the classic).
